    Creating an array containing words
arr mak a1 < Hello World. This program is written in DOSB! DOSB is a small instruction-based programming language with many
             use cases as it has the same features as modern programming languages like lua, C, C++ and python with the syntax of assembly! >

    converting that array to a single string -> putting it into r1-register
str con !a1 r1

    overwriting the file ./testsave.txt with the content of the r1-register
io write ./testsave.txt ovr r1

    reading the content of the ./testsave.txt 
io read ./testsave.txt

    printing out the result of the file-read
prt acc ::END
